ai.skymind.pipelines.executioner.inference

Interface InferenceExecutioner<MODEL_LOADER_TYPE extends ModelLoader<MODEL_TYPE>,INPUT_TYPE,OUTPUT_TYPE,CONFIG_TYPE,MODEL_TYPE>

  • Type Parameters:
    MODEL_LOADER_TYPE - the model loader type to use for loading models of MODEL_TYPE
    INPUT_TYPE - the input data to the threadpool
    OUTPUT_TYPE - the output type of the threadpool
    CONFIG_TYPE - the configuration for the thread pool
    MODEL_TYPE - the model type to use for inference

    public interface InferenceExecutioner<MODEL_LOADER_TYPE extends ModelLoader<MODEL_TYPE>,INPUT_TYPE,OUTPUT_TYPE,CONFIG_TYPE,MODEL_TYPE>
    An InferenceExecutioner handles wrapping a model thread pool such as ParallelInference for thread safe inference allowing different modes of inference including batch accumulation or 1 at a time processing of data This includes handling a specific model type, a specified input type such as INDArray and a configuration such as the ParallelInferenceConfig
    Author:
    Adam Gibson
